{{!-- One move row: the rollable <li> wrapper + the shared move-item body. Shared by the moves tab
      (move-group) and the major-arcana card (arcanum-cards) so the roll wiring stays identical — a
      rollable, acquired move gets `.item[data-item-id]` so the sheet's roll handler resolves the OWNED
      move item (full description + 10+/7-9/6- result tiers) instead of a bare stat roll. Context is a
      MoveSnapshot; params: showCheck, categoryKey, allowAdditional (forwarded to move-item). --}}
{{#if (and (gt selection.value 0) rollStat)}}
<li class="item stonetop-item" data-item-id="{{ownedId}}">
{{else}}
<li class="stonetop-item">
{{/if}}
	{{> "stonetop.move-item" showCheck=showCheck categoryKey=categoryKey allowAdditional=allowAdditional}}
</li>
